		<part id="practices-mocking">
			<title>Mocking: API First based on API Descriptions</title>
			<part id="practices-mocking-why">
				<title>Why Mocking?</title>
				<slide id="practices-collaborative-design">
					<title>Faster Feedback Cycles</title>
					<img src="API-design-collaboration.png" class="fullsize-left" />
				</slide>
				<slide id="practices-mocking-use-cases">
					<title>Use Cases for API Mocking</title>
					<ul>
						<li><em>Frontend/Backend Parallel Work:</em> Build UIs before the backend exists</li>
						<li><em>Design-First Validation:</em> Try out the API contract early</li>
						<li><em>Demos and Prototyping:</em> Show stable behavior without real servers</li>
						<li><em>Developer Onboarding:</em> Let new devs explore APIs instantly</li>
						<li><em>Integration &amp; Error Testing:</em> Simulate edge cases and failures safely</li>
					</ul>
				</slide>
			</part>
