				<slide id="practices-mocking-how">
					<title>How to use a Mock Tool</title>
					<ul>
						<li>Mocking tools come as local or hosted versions</li>
						<li>OpenAPI serves as the input for the mocking tool</li>
						<ul>
							<li>The tool looks for paths, methods, and responses</li>
							<li><em>Examples</em> and <em>schemas</em> are used for sending responses</li>
						</ul>
						<li>Mock servers can be started with OpenAPI as their only input</li>
						<li>Additional options allow to fine-tune the server's behavior</li>
					</ul>
